Even if an experimental vaccine seems so far to be able to reduce the mortality rate of Ebola, no treatment has yet been sufficiently effective to treat the existing infection.
Even if the administration of a cocktail of antibodies, ZMapp, had initially shown promising results on the ground, formal studies have shown that its ability to limit deaths did not meet expectations.
In the PALM trial, ZMapp was used as a control, which means that the scientists used it as a reference and compared it to the other three treatments.
The American Gymnastics Federation supports the letter of the United States Olympic Committee and accepts the absolute necessity of the Olympic family to promote a safe environment for all our athletes.
We agree with the statement of the USOC (United States Olympic Committee) that the interests of our athletes and our clubs, as well as their sport, could be better served by going forward and proceeding with significant changes within our organization, rather than revoking accreditation.
USA Gymnastics supports an independent investigation that could shed light on how the abuse of power described so courageously by Larry Nassar’s survivors could have gone unnoticed for so long and adopts all necessary and appropriate changes.
USA Gymnastics and the USOC have the same goal: to make gymnastics, as well as other sports, as safe as possible so that athletes can pursue their dreams in a safe, positive and responsible environment.
Throughout the 1960s, Brzezinski worked for John F. Kennedy as an advisor, and then for the administration of Lyndon B. Johnson.
During the 1976 selections, he advised Carter on foreign policy, then served as NSA advisor from 1977 to 1981, succeeding Henry Kissinger.
During his tenure at the NSA, he helped Carter to resolve international issues such as the Camp David Accords, in 1978, the normalization of relations between the United States and China in the late 1970s, the Iranian Revolution and its consequences such as the hostage crisis in Iran, in 1979, and the Soviet invasion of Afghanistan, in 1979.
